Headers for web requests headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.5', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1', 'Cache-Control': 'no-cache', 'Pragma': 'no-cache' } # Function to perform search and analyze results def perform_search(query, search_index): search_base_url = 'https://html.duckduckgo.com/html/' print(f'\n--- SEARCH {search_index}: {query} ---') try: params = {'q': query} response = requests.get(search_base_url, params=params, headers=headers, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: # Save raw HTML for analysis filename = f'martineau_search_{search_index:02d}_{query.replace(" ", "_").replace("\'", "").replace('"', "")[:40]}.html' filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) with open(filepath, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'Saved: {filepath}') # Parse for relevant results soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser') # Look for result links with historical book information result_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href') text = link.get_text().strip() # Filter for highly relevant results if href and text and len(text) > 15: text_lower = text.lower() relevance_score = 0 # High-value terms for Martineau's historical work high_value_terms = [ ('harriet martineau', 3), ('martineau', 2), ('1846', 3), ('1840', 2), ('convention of london', 4), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('crisis', 1), ('european peace', 3), ('diplomatic', 2), ('diplomacy', 2), ('four volume', 3), ('1877', 2), ('1878', 2), ('history', 1), ('historical', 1), ('peace', 1), ('europe', 1) ] # Book-specific terms book_terms = [ ('history of england', 3), ('history of the peace', 4), ('eastern question', 3), ('thirty years peace', 4), ('england and her soldiers', 2), ('biographical sketches', 2) ] # Calculate relevance score for term, score in high_value_terms + book_terms: if term in text_lower: relevance_score += score # Additional scoring for URL domains if href: href_lower = href.lower() if any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['archive.org', 'gutenberg.org', 'hathitrust.org', 'google.com/books']): relevance_score += 3 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['wikipedia.org', 'britannica.com', 'jstor.org']): relevance_score += 2 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['amazon.com', 'worldcat.org', 'goodreads.com']): relevance_score += 1 if relevance_score >= 3: # Only include highly relevant results result_links.append({ 'url': href, 'text': text[:400], # Longer text for better analysis 'relevance_score': relevance_score }) # Sort by relevance score result_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) search_results[query] = { 'html_file': filepath, 'status_code': response.status_code, 'relevant_links': result_links[:20], # Top 20 most relevant 'total_links_found': len(result_links) } print(f'Found {len(result_links)} highly relevant links') if result_links: print('Top results:') for i, link in enumerate(result_links[:5], 1): print(f' {i}. Score {link["relevance_score"]}: {link["text"][:120]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') time.sleep(2) # Rate limiting return True else: print(f'Failed: HTTP {response.status_code}') return False except Exception as e: print(f'Error: {str(e)}') return False # Perform all searches print('\n=== EXECUTING SEARCHES ===') successful_searches = 0 for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): if perform_search(query, i): successful_searches += 1 # Brief pause between searches if i < len(search_queries): time.sleep(1) print(f'\n=== STEP 2: ANALYZING SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK IDENTIFICATION ===') print(f'Successful searches: {successful_searches}/{len(search_queries)}') # Compile and analyze all findings high_priority_findings = [] book_candidates = {} historical_terms_frequency = {} # Key terms to track for book identification key_terms = [ 'history of england', 'history of the peace', 'thirty years peace', 'eastern question', 'convention of london', 'egyptian crisis', 'ottoman crisis', 'four volume', '1877', '1878', '1846', '1840' ] print('\n--- ANALYZING ALL SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK PATTERNS ---') for query, results in search_results.items(): print(f'\nQuery: "{query}"') print(f' Relevant links: {results["total_links_found"]}') for link in results['relevant_links']: text_lower = link['text'].lower() # Check for key historical terms found_terms = [] for term in key_terms: if term in text_lower: found_terms.append(term) historical_terms_frequency[term] = historical_terms_frequency.get(term, 0) + 1 # High-priority: Contains multiple key terms if len(found_terms) >= 3: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'HIGH - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üéØ HIGH PRIORITY: {len(found_terms)} key terms found: {found_terms}') # Try to extract potential book titles text_lines = link['text'].split('\n') for line in text_lines: line_lower = line.lower().strip() if ('history' in line_lower and ('martineau' in line_lower or len(line.strip()) > 20) and any(term in line_lower for term in ['peace', 'england', 'thirty years'])): # This might be a book title potential_title = line.strip()[:200] if potential_title not in book_candidates: book_candidates[potential_title] = [] book_candidates[potential_title].append({ 'query': query, 'url': link['url'], 'terms': found_terms, 'score': link['relevance_score'] }) elif len(found_terms) >= 2: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'MEDIUM - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üìç MEDIUM: {len(found_terms)} key terms: {found_terms}') print(f'\n=== STEP 3: HISTORICAL TERMS FREQUENCY ANALYSIS ===') print(f'Total high-priority findings: {len(high_priority_findings)}') print(f'Potential book candidates identified: {len(book_candidates)}') if historical_terms_frequency: print('\nHistorical terms frequency:') sorted_terms = sorted(historical_terms_frequency.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True) for term, count in sorted_terms: print(f' {term}: {count} mentions') else: print('\nNo specific historical terms clearly identified') print(f'\n=== STEP 4: BOOK CANDIDATE ANALYSIS ===') if book_candidates: print(f'\nAnalyzing {len(book_candidates)} potential book titles:') # Sort by evidence strength sorted_candidates = sorted(book_candidates.items(), key=lambda x: len(x[1]), reverse=True) for title, evidence_list in sorted_candidates[:10]: # Top 10 candidates print(f'\nüìö CANDIDATE: {title}') print(f' Evidence sources: {len(evidence_list)}') # Aggregate terms and scores all_terms = set() total_score = 0 sources = set() for evidence in evidence_list: all_terms.update(evidence['terms']) total_score += evidence['score'] sources.add(evidence['query']) print(f' Key terms found: {sorted(list(all_terms))}') print(f' Total relevance score: {total_score}') print(f' Search queries: {len(sources)}') # Check for four-volume edition indicators title_lower = title.lower() if any(indicator in title_lower for indicator in ['four volume', '4 volume', 'vol.', 'volume']): print(f' ‚úì VOLUME INDICATOR FOUND') # Check for 1877-1878 date indicators if any(year in title_lower for year in ['1877', '1878']): print(f' ‚úì TARGET PUBLICATION YEARS FOUND') print('-' * 100) else: print('\n‚ö† No clear book candidates identified from search results') print(f'\n=== STEP 5: DETAILED ANALYSIS OF HIGH-PRIORITY FINDINGS ===') if high_priority_findings: # Sort by priority and score high_priority_findings.sort(key=lambda x: (x['priority'].startswith('HIGH'), len(x['key_terms_found']), x['score']), reverse=True) print(f'\nAnalyzing top {min(10, len(high_priority_findings))} high-priority findings:') for i, finding in enumerate(high_priority_findings[:10], 1): print(f'\nüîç FINDING {i} - {finding["priority"]} (Score: {finding["score"]})') print(f'Query: {finding["query"]}') print(f'Key terms: {finding["key_terms_found"]}') print(f'URL: {finding["url"]}') print(f'Text: {finding["text"][:500]}...') # Try Google Books API for more specific results print(f'\n=== STEP 6: GOOGLE BOOKS API SEARCH ===') google_books_queries = [ 'Harriet Martineau History of the Peace 1877', 'Martineau History England four volumes 1878', 'Harriet Martineau Convention London 1840', 'Martineau Egyptian Ottoman crisis 1846' ] books_api_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(google_books_queries, 1): print(f'\n--- Google Books API Query {i}: {query} ---') try: api_url = 'https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes' params = { 'q': query, 'maxResults': 20, 'printType': 'books' } response = requests.get(api_url, params=params, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: data = response.json() if 'items' in data: print(f'Found {len(data["items"])} books') for book in data['items']: volume_info = book.get('volumeInfo', {}) title = volume_info.get('title', '') authors = volume_info.get('authors', []) published_date = volume_info.get('publishedDate', '') publisher = volume_info.get('publisher', '') description = volume_info.get('description', '') # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json import time from urllib.parse import quote_plus print('=== SEARCHING FOR HARRIET MARTINEAU\'S BOOK ON EUROPEAN PEACE ENDING 1846 ===') print('Objective: Find Martineau book analyzing European peace period ending 1846') print('Key elements: Convention of London 1840, Egyptian-Ottoman crisis') print('Target: Four-volume edition published 1877-1878') print('\n' + '='*100 + '\n') # Ensure workspace directory exists os.makedirs('workspace', exist_ok=True) # Define comprehensive search queries based on the PLAN search_queries = [ 'Harriet Martineau European peace 1846', 'Convention of London 1840 Martineau', 'Egyptian-Ottoman crisis Martineau book', 'Martineau four-volume edition 1877 1878', 'Harriet Martineau diplomatic history Europe 1840s', 'Martineau Convention London Egyptian crisis', 'Harriet Martineau European diplomacy 1846', 'Martineau Ottoman Empire Egypt 1840 book', 'Harriet Martineau history peace Europe 1840s', 'Martineau four volumes 1877 1878 European history' ] print('=== STEP 1: CONDUCTING TARGETED SEARCHES FOR MARTINEAU\'S HISTORICAL WORK ===') print(f'Total search queries: {len(search_queries)}') print('\nSearch queries:') for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f' {i:2d}. {query}') search_results = {} # Headers for web requests headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.5', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1', 'Cache-Control': 'no-cache', 'Pragma': 'no-cache' } # Function to perform search and analyze results def perform_search(query, search_index): search_base_url = 'https://html.duckduckgo.com/html/' print(f'\n--- SEARCH {search_index}: {query} ---') try: params = {'q': query} response = requests.get(search_base_url, params=params, headers=headers, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: # Save raw HTML for analysis filename = f'martineau_search_{search_index:02d}_{query.replace(" ", "_").replace("\'", "").replace('"', "")[:40]}.html' filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) with open(filepath, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'Saved: {filepath}') # Parse for relevant results soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser') # Look for result links with historical book information result_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href') text = link.get_text().strip() # Filter for highly relevant results if href and text and len(text) > 15: text_lower = text.lower() relevance_score = 0 # High-value terms for Martineau's historical work high_value_terms = [ ('harriet martineau', 3), ('martineau', 2), ('1846', 3), ('1840', 2), ('convention of london', 4), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('crisis', 1), ('european peace', 3), ('diplomatic', 2), ('diplomacy', 2), ('four volume', 3), ('1877', 2), ('1878', 2), ('history', 1), ('historical', 1), ('peace', 1), ('europe', 1) ] # Book-specific terms book_terms = [ ('history of england', 3), ('history of the peace', 4), ('eastern question', 3), ('thirty years peace', 4), ('england and her soldiers', 2), ('biographical sketches', 2) ] # Calculate relevance score for term, score in high_value_terms + book_terms: if term in text_lower: relevance_score += score # Additional scoring for URL domains if href: href_lower = href.lower() if any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['archive.org', 'gutenberg.org', 'hathitrust.org', 'google.com/books']): relevance_score += 3 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['wikipedia.org', 'britannica.com', 'jstor.org']): relevance_score += 2 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['amazon.com', 'worldcat.org', 'goodreads.com']): relevance_score += 1 if relevance_score >= 3: # Only include highly relevant results result_links.append({ 'url': href, 'text': text[:400], # Longer text for better analysis 'relevance_score': relevance_score }) # Sort by relevance score result_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) search_results[query] = { 'html_file': filepath, 'status_code': response.status_code, 'relevant_links': result_links[:20], # Top 20 most relevant 'total_links_found': len(result_links) } print(f'Found {len(result_links)} highly relevant links') if result_links: print('Top results:') for i, link in enumerate(result_links[:5], 1): print(f' {i}. Score {link["relevance_score"]}: {link["text"][:120]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') time.sleep(2) # Rate limiting return True else: print(f'Failed: HTTP {response.status_code}') return False except Exception as e: print(f'Error: {str(e)}') return False # Perform all searches print('\n=== EXECUTING SEARCHES ===') successful_searches = 0 for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): if perform_search(query, i): successful_searches += 1 # Brief pause between searches if i < len(search_queries): time.sleep(1) print(f'\n=== STEP 2: ANALYZING SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK IDENTIFICATION ===') print(f'Successful searches: {successful_searches}/{len(search_queries)}') # Compile and analyze all findings high_priority_findings = [] book_candidates = {} historical_terms_frequency = {} # Key terms to track for book identification key_terms = [ 'history of england', 'history of the peace', 'thirty years peace', 'eastern question', 'convention of london', 'egyptian crisis', 'ottoman crisis', 'four volume', '1877', '1878', '1846', '1840' ] print('\n--- ANALYZING ALL SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK PATTERNS ---') for query, results in search_results.items(): print(f'\nQuery: "{query}"') print(f' Relevant links: {results["total_links_found"]}') for link in results['relevant_links']: text_lower = link['text'].lower() # Check for key historical terms found_terms = [] for term in key_terms: if term in text_lower: found_terms.append(term) historical_terms_frequency[term] = historical_terms_frequency.get(term, 0) + 1 # High-priority: Contains multiple key terms if len(found_terms) >= 3: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'HIGH - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üéØ HIGH PRIORITY: {len(found_terms)} key terms found: {found_terms}') # Try to extract potential book titles text_lines = link['text'].split('\n') for line in text_lines: line_lower = line.lower().strip() if ('history' in line_lower and ('martineau' in line_lower or len(line.strip()) > 20) and any(term in line_lower for term in ['peace', 'england', 'thirty years'])): # This might be a book title potential_title = line.strip()[:200] if potential_title not in book_candidates: book_candidates[potential_title] = [] book_candidates[potential_title].append({ 'query': query, 'url': link['url'], 'terms': found_terms, 'score': link['relevance_score'] }) elif len(found_terms) >= 2: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'MEDIUM - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üìç MEDIUM: {len(found_terms)} key terms: {found_terms}') print(f'\n=== STEP 3: HISTORICAL TERMS FREQUENCY ANALYSIS ===') print(f'Total high-priority findings: {len(high_priority_findings)}') print(f'Potential book candidates identified: {len(book_candidates)}') if historical_terms_frequency: print('\nHistorical terms frequency:') sorted_terms = sorted(historical_terms_frequency.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True) for term, count in sorted_terms: print(f' {term}: {count} mentions') else: print('\nNo specific historical terms clearly identified') print(f'\n=== STEP 4: BOOK CANDIDATE ANALYSIS ===') if book_candidates: print(f'\nAnalyzing {len(book_candidates)} potential book titles:') # Sort by evidence strength sorted_candidates = sorted(book_candidates.items(), key=lambda x: len(x[1]), reverse=True) for title, evidence_list in sorted_candidates[:10]: # Top 10 candidates print(f'\nüìö CANDIDATE: {title}') print(f' Evidence sources: {len(evidence_list)}') # Aggregate terms and scores all_terms = set() total_score = 0 sources = set() for evidence in evidence_list: all_terms.update(evidence['terms']) total_score += evidence['score'] sources.add(evidence['query']) print(f' Key terms found: {sorted(list(all_terms))}') print(f' Total relevance score: {total_score}') print(f' Search queries: {len(sources)}') # Check for four-volume edition indicators title_lower = title.lower() if any(indicator in title_lower for indicator in ['four volume', '4 volume', 'vol.', 'volume']): print(f' ‚úì VOLUME INDICATOR FOUND') # Check for 1877-1878 date indicators if any(year in title_lower for year in ['1877', '1878']): print(f' ‚úì TARGET PUBLICATION YEARS FOUND') print('-' * 100) else: print('\n‚ö† No clear book candidates identified from search results') print(f'\n=== STEP 5: DETAILED ANALYSIS OF HIGH-PRIORITY FINDINGS ===') if high_priority_findings: # Sort by priority and score high_priority_findings.sort(key=lambda x: (x['priority'].startswith('HIGH'), len(x['key_terms_found']), x['score']), reverse=True) print(f'\nAnalyzing top {min(10, len(high_priority_findings))} high-priority findings:') for i, finding in enumerate(high_priority_findings[:10], 1): print(f'\nüîç FINDING {i} - {finding["priority"]} (Score: {finding["score"]})') print(f'Query: {finding["query"]}') print(f'Key terms: {finding["key_terms_found"]}') print(f'URL: {finding["url"]}') print(f'Text: {finding["text"][:500]}...') # Look for specific book title patterns in the text text_lower = finding['text'].lower() # Common Martineau book title patterns martineau_patterns = [ 'history of england', 'history of the peace', 'thirty years peace', 'biographical sketches', 'eastern question' ] found_patterns = [] for pattern in martineau_patterns: if pattern in text_lower: found_patterns.append(pattern) if found_patterns: print(f' üìñ BOOK TITLE PATTERNS: {found_patterns}') print('-' * 120) else: print('\n‚ö† No high-priority findings identified') # Try Google Books API for more specific results print(f'\n=== STEP 6: GOOGLE BOOKS API SEARCH ===') google_books_queries = [ 'Harriet Martineau History of the Peace 1877', 'Martineau History England four volumes 1878', 'Harriet Martineau Convention London 1840', 'Martineau Egyptian Ottoman crisis 1846' ] books_api_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(google_books_queries, 1): print(f'\n--- Google Books API Query {i}: {query} ---') try: api_url = 'https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes' params = { 'q': query, 'maxResults': 20, 'printType': 'books' } response = requests.get(api_url, params=params, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: data = response.json() if 'items' in data: print(f'Found {len(data["items"])} books') for book in data['items']: volume_info = book.get('volumeInfo', {}) title = volume_info.get('title', '') authors = volume_info.get('authors', []) published_date = volume_info.get('publishedDate', '') publisher = volume_info.get('publisher', '') description = volume_info.get('description', '') # Check if this matches our criteria title_lower = title.lower() authors_str = ' '.join(authors).lower() if authors else '' desc_lower = description.lower() # Look for Martineau and relevant terms if 'martineau' in authors_str or 'martineau' in title_lower: relevance_score = 0 # Score based on key terms key_indicators = [ ('1877', 3), ('1878', 3), ('1846', 2), ('1840', 2), ('history', 2), ('peace', 2), ('convention', 2), ('london', 1), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('four volume', 4), ('volume', 1) ] combined_text = f'{title_lower} {desc_lower} {published_date}' for indicator, score in key_indicators: if indicator in combined_text: relevance_score += score if relevance_score >= 3: # Significant relevance print(f'\nüéØ RELEVANT BOOK FOUND (Score: {relevance_score})!') print(f'Title: {title}') print(f'Authors: {authors}') print(f'Publisher: {publisher}') print(f'Published: {published_date}') if description: print(f'Description: {description[:300]}...') books_api_results.append({ 'title': title, 'authors': authors, 'publisher': publisher, 'published_date': published_date, 'description': description, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'query': query, 'source': 'Google Books API' }) else: print('No books found in API response') else: print(f'API request failed: {response.status_code}') time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting except Exception as e: print(f'Error with Google Books API: {str(e)}') # Save comprehensive analysis analysis_results = { 'search_objective': 'Find Harriet Martineau book on European peace ending 1846', 'key_elements': { 'period_ending': 1846, 'convention_of_london': 1840, 'egyptian_ottoman_crisis': True, 'four_volume_edition': '1877-1878' }, 'search_summary': { 'total_queries': len(search_queries), 'successful_searches': successful_searches, 'total_relevant_links': sum(len(r['relevant_links']) for r in search_results.values()), 'google_books_results': len(books_api_results) }, 'analysis_results': { 'high_priority_findings': len(high_priority_findings), 'book_candidates': len(book_candidates), 'historical_terms_frequency': historical_terms_frequency, 'top_book_candidates': list(book_candidates.keys())[:5] if book_candidates else [] }, 'high_priority_findings': high_priority_findings[:15], # Headers for web requests headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.5', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1', 'Cache-Control': 'no-cache', 'Pragma': 'no-cache' } # Function to perform search and analyze results - FIXED QUOTE ESCAPING def perform_search(query, search_index): search_base_url = 'https://html.duckduckgo.com/html/' print(f'\n--- SEARCH {search_index}: {query} ---') try: params = {'q': query} response = requests.get(search_base_url, params=params, headers=headers, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: # Save raw HTML for analysis - FIXED FILENAME GENERATION clean_query = query.replace(' ', '_').replace("'", '').replace('"', '').replace('/', '_') filename = f"martineau_search_{search_index:02d}_{clean_query[:40]}.html" filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) with open(filepath, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'Saved: {filepath}') # Parse for relevant results soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser') # Look for result links with historical book information result_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href') text = link.get_text().strip() # Filter for highly relevant results if href and text and len(text) > 15: text_lower = text.lower() relevance_score = 0 # High-value terms for Martineau's historical work high_value_terms = [ ('harriet martineau', 3), ('martineau', 2), ('1846', 3), ('1840', 2), ('convention of london', 4), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('crisis', 1), ('european peace', 3), ('diplomatic', 2), ('diplomacy', 2), ('four volume', 3), ('1877', 2), ('1878', 2), ('history', 1), ('historical', 1), ('peace', 1), ('europe', 1) ] # Book-specific terms book_terms = [ ('history of england', 3), ('history of the peace', 4), ('eastern question', 3), ('thirty years peace', 4), ('england and her soldiers', 2), ('biographical sketches', 2) ] # Calculate relevance score for term, score in high_value_terms + book_terms: if term in text_lower: relevance_score += score # Additional scoring for URL domains if href: href_lower = href.lower() if any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['archive.org', 'gutenberg.org', 'hathitrust.org', 'google.com/books']): relevance_score += 3 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['wikipedia.org', 'britannica.com', 'jstor.org']): relevance_score += 2 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['amazon.com', 'worldcat.org', 'goodreads.com']): relevance_score += 1 if relevance_score >= 3: # Only include highly relevant results result_links.append({ 'url': href, 'text': text[:400], # Longer text for better analysis 'relevance_score': relevance_score }) # Sort by relevance score result_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) search_results[query] = { 'html_file': filepath, 'status_code': response.status_code, 'relevant_links': result_links[:20], # Top 20 most relevant 'total_links_found': len(result_links) } print(f'Found {len(result_links)} highly relevant links') if result_links: print('Top results:') for i, link in enumerate(result_links[:5], 1): print(f' {i}. Score {link["relevance_score"]}: {link["text"][:120]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') time.sleep(2) # Rate limiting return True else: print(f'Failed: HTTP {response.status_code}') return False except Exception as e: print(f'Error: {str(e)}') return False # Perform all searches print('\n=== EXECUTING SEARCHES ===') successful_searches = 0 for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): if perform_search(query, i): successful_searches += 1 # Brief pause between searches if i < len(search_queries): time.sleep(1) print(f'\n=== STEP 2: ANALYZING SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK IDENTIFICATION ===') print(f'Successful searches: {successful_searches}/{len(search_queries)}') # Compile and analyze all findings high_priority_findings = [] book_candidates = {} historical_terms_frequency = {} # Key terms to track for book identification key_terms = [ 'history of england', 'history of the peace', 'thirty years peace', 'eastern question', 'convention of london', 'egyptian crisis', 'ottoman crisis', 'four volume', '1877', '1878', '1846', '1840' ] print('\n--- ANALYZING ALL SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK PATTERNS ---') for query, results in search_results.items(): print(f'\nQuery: "{query}"') print(f' Relevant links: {results["total_links_found"]}') for link in results['relevant_links']: text_lower = link['text'].lower() # Check for key historical terms found_terms = [] for term in key_terms: if term in text_lower: found_terms.append(term) historical_terms_frequency[term] = historical_terms_frequency.get(term, 0) + 1 # High-priority: Contains multiple key terms if len(found_terms) >= 3: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'HIGH - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üéØ HIGH PRIORITY: {len(found_terms)} key terms found: {found_terms}') # Try to extract potential book titles text_lines = link['text'].split('\n') for line in text_lines: line_lower = line.lower().strip() if ('history' in line_lower and ('martineau' in line_lower or len(line.strip()) > 20) and any(term in line_lower for term in ['peace', 'england', 'thirty years'])): # This might be a book title potential_title = line.strip()[:200] if potential_title not in book_candidates: book_candidates[potential_title] = [] book_candidates[potential_title].append({ 'query': query, 'url': link['url'], 'terms': found_terms, 'score': link['relevance_score'] }) elif len(found_terms) >= 2: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'MEDIUM - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üìç MEDIUM: {len(found_terms)} key terms: {found_terms}') print(f'\n=== STEP 3: HISTORICAL TERMS FREQUENCY ANALYSIS ===') print(f'Total high-priority findings: {len(high_priority_findings)}') print(f'Potential book candidates identified: {len(book_candidates)}') if historical_terms_frequency: print('\nHistorical terms frequency:') sorted_terms = sorted(historical_terms_frequency.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True) for term, count in sorted_terms: print(f' {term}: {count} mentions') else: print('\nNo specific historical terms clearly identified') print(f'\n=== STEP 4: BOOK CANDIDATE ANALYSIS ===') if book_candidates: print(f'\nAnalyzing {len(book_candidates)} potential book titles:') # Sort by evidence strength sorted_candidates = sorted(book_candidates.items(), key=lambda x: len(x[1]), reverse=True) for title, evidence_list in sorted_candidates[:10]: # Top 10 candidates print(f'\nüìö CANDIDATE: {title}') print(f' Evidence sources: {len(evidence_list)}') # Aggregate terms and scores all_terms = set() total_score = 0 sources = set() for evidence in evidence_list: all_terms.update(evidence['terms']) total_score += evidence['score'] sources.add(evidence['query']) print(f' Key terms found: {sorted(list(all_terms))}') print(f' Total relevance score: {total_score}') print(f' Search queries: {len(sources)}') # Check for four-volume edition indicators title_lower = title.lower() if any(indicator in title_lower for indicator in ['four volume', '4 volume', 'vol.', 'volume']): print(f' ‚úì VOLUME INDICATOR FOUND') # Check for 1877-1878 date indicators if any(year in title_lower for year in ['1877', '1878']): print(f' ‚úì TARGET PUBLICATION YEARS FOUND') print('-' * 100) else: print('\n‚ö† No clear book candidates identified from search results') print(f'\n=== STEP 5: DETAILED ANALYSIS OF HIGH-PRIORITY FINDINGS ===') if high_priority_findings: # Sort by priority and score high_priority_findings.sort(key=lambda x: (x['priority'].startswith('HIGH'), len(x['key_terms_found']), x['score']), reverse=True) print(f'\nAnalyzing top {min(10, len(high_priority_findings))} high-priority findings:') for i, finding in enumerate(high_priority_findings[:10], 1): print(f'\nüîç FINDING {i} - {finding["priority"]} (Score: {finding["score"]})') print(f'Query: {finding["query"]}') print(f'Key terms: {finding["key_terms_found"]}') print(f'URL: {finding["url"]}') print(f'Text: {finding["text"][:500]}...') # Look for specific book title patterns in the text text_lower = finding['text'].lower() # Common Martineau book title patterns martineau_patterns = [ 'history of england', 'history of the peace', 'thirty years peace', 'biographical sketches', 'eastern question' ] found_patterns = [] for pattern in martineau_patterns: if pattern in text_lower: found_patterns.append(pattern) if found_patterns: print(f' üìñ BOOK TITLE PATTERNS: {found_patterns}') print('-' * 120) else: print('\n‚ö† No high-priority findings identified') # Try Google Books API for more specific results print(f'\n=== STEP 6: GOOGLE BOOKS API SEARCH ===') google_books_queries = [ 'Harriet Martineau History of the Peace 1877', 'Martineau History England four volumes 1878', 'Harriet Martineau Convention London 1840', 'Martineau Egyptian Ottoman crisis 1846' ] books_api_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(google_books_queries, 1): print(f'\n--- Google Books API Query {i}: {query} ---') try: api_url = 'https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes' params = { 'q': query, 'maxResults': 20, 'printType': 'books' } response = requests.get(api_url, params=params, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: data = response.json() if 'items' in data: print(f'Found {len(data["items"])} books') for book in data['items']: volume_info = book.get('volumeInfo', {}) title = volume_info.get('title', '') authors = volume_info.get('authors', []) published_date = volume_info.get('publishedDate', '') publisher = volume_info.get('publisher', '') description = volume_info.get('description', '') # Check if this matches our criteria title_lower = title.lower() authors_str = ' '.join(authors).lower() if authors else '' desc_lower = description.lower() # Look for Martineau and relevant terms if 'martineau' in authors_str or 'martineau' in title_lower: relevance_score = 0 # Score based on key terms key_indicators = [ ('1877', 3), ('1878', 3), ('1846', 2), ('1840', 2), ('history', 2), ('peace', 2), ('convention', 2), ('london', 1), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('four volume', 4), ('volume', 1) ] combined_text = f'{title_lower} {desc_lower} {published_date}' for indicator, score in key_indicators: if indicator in combined_text: relevance_score += score if relevance_score >= 3: # Significant relevance print(f'\nüéØ RELEVANT BOOK FOUND (Score: {relevance_score})!') print(f'Title: {title}') print(f'Authors: {authors}') print(f'Publisher: {publisher}') print(f'Published: {published_date}') if description: print(f'Description: {description[:300]}...') books_api_results.append({ 'title': title, 'authors': authors, 'publisher': publisher, 'published_date': published_date, 'description': description, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'query': query, 'source': 'Google Books API' }) else: print('No books found in API response') else: print(f'API request failed: {response.status_code}') time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting except Exception as e: print(f'Error with Google Books API: {str(e)}') # Save comprehensive analysis analysis_results = { 'search_objective': 'Find Harriet Martineau book on European peace ending 1846', 'key_elements': { 'period_ending': 1846, 'convention_of_london': 1840, 'egyptian_ottoman_crisis': True, 'four_volume_edition': '1877-1878' }, 'search_summary': { 'total_queries': len(search_queries), 'successful_searches': successful_searches, 'total_relevant_links': sum(len(r['relevant_links']) for r in search_results.values()), 'google_books_results': len(books_api_results) }, 'analysis_results': { 'high_priority_findings': len(high_priority_findings), 'book_candidates': len(book_candidates), 'historical_terms_frequency': historical_terms_frequency, 'top_book_candidates': list(book_candidates.keys())[:5] if book_candidates else [] }, 'high_priority_findings': high_priority_findings[:15], # Top 15 findings 'google_books_results': books_api_results, 'search_queries_used': search_queries, 'analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } analysis_file = 'workspace/martineau_european_peace_book_search_analysis.json' with open(analysis_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\n*** MARTINEAU BOOK SEARCH ANALYSIS COMPLETE ***') print(f'‚úì Conducted {successful_searches} successful web searches') print(f'‚úì Analyzed {sum(len(r["relevant_links"]) for r in search_results.values())} relevant results') print(f'‚úì Found {len(high_priority_findings)} high-priority findings') print(f'‚úì Identified {len(book_candidates)} potential book candidates') print(f'‚úì Found {len(books_api_results)} relevant books via Google Books API') print(f'‚úì Comprehensive analysis saved to: {analysis_file}') # Summary of most promising leads if books_api_results: top_book = max(books_api_results, key=lambda x: x['relevance_score']) print(f'\nüéØ MOST PROMISING GOOGLE BOOKS RESULT:') print(f'Title: {top_book["title"]}') print(f'Authors: {top_book["authors"]}') print(f'Published: {top_book["published_date"]}') print(f'Relevance Score: {top_book["relevance_score"]}') elif book_candidates: top_candidate = max(book_candidates.items(), key=lambda x: len(x[1])) print(f'\nüéØ MOST PROMISING BOOK CANDIDATE:') print(f'Title: {top_candidate[0]}') print(f'Evidence sources: {len(top_candidate[1])}') elif high_priority_findings: top_finding = high_priority_findings[0] print(f'\nüéØ MOST PROMISING FINDING:') print(f'Priority: {top_finding["priority"]}') print(f'Key terms: {top_finding["key_terms_found"]}') print(f'URL: {top_finding["url"]}') else: print(f'\n‚ö† No definitive book identification in initial search') print('Recommend manual investigation of saved search results') print('\n=== NEXT STEPS ===') print('1. Perform all searches print('\n=== EXECUTING SEARCHES ===') successful_searches = 0 for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): if perform_search(query, i): successful_searches += 1 # Brief pause between searches if i < len(search_queries): time.sleep(1) print(f'\n=== STEP 2: ANALYZING SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK IDENTIFICATION ===') print(f'Successful searches: {successful_searches}/{len(search_queries)}') # Compile and analyze all findings high_priority_findings = [] book_candidates = {} historical_terms_frequency = {} # Key terms to track for book identification key_terms = [ 'history of england', 'history of the peace', 'thirty years peace', 'eastern question', 'convention of london', 'egyptian crisis', 'ottoman crisis', 'four volume', '1877', '1878', '1846', '1840' ] print('\n--- ANALYZING ALL SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK PATTERNS ---') for query, results in search_results.items(): print(f'\nQuery: "{query}"') print(f' Relevant links: {results["total_links_found"]}') for link in results['relevant_links']: text_lower = link['text'].lower() # Check for key historical terms found_terms = [] for term in key_terms: if term in text_lower: found_terms.append(term) historical_terms_frequency[term] = historical_terms_frequency.get(term, 0) + 1 # High-priority: Contains multiple key terms if len(found_terms) >= 3: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'HIGH - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üéØ HIGH PRIORITY: {len(found_terms)} key terms found: {found_terms}') # Try to extract potential book titles text_lines = link['text'].split('\n') for line in text_lines: line_lower = line.lower().strip() if ('history' in line_lower and ('martineau' in line_lower or len(line.strip()) > 20) and any(term in line_lower for term in ['peace', 'england', 'thirty years'])): # This might be a book title potential_title = line.strip()[:200] if potential_title not in book_candidates: book_candidates[potential_title] = [] book_candidates[potential_title].append({ 'query': query, 'url': link['url'], 'terms': found_terms, 'score': link['relevance_score'] }) elif len(found_terms) >= 2: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'MEDIUM - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üìç MEDIUM: {len(found_terms)} key terms: {found_terms}') print(f'\n=== STEP 3: HISTORICAL TERMS FREQUENCY ANALYSIS ===') print(f'Total high-priority findings: {len(high_priority_findings)}') print(f'Potential book candidates identified: {len(book_candidates)}') if historical_terms_frequency: print('\nHistorical terms frequency:') sorted_terms = sorted(historical_terms_frequency.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True) for term, count in sorted_terms: print(f' {term}: {count} mentions') else: print('\nNo specific historical terms clearly identified') print(f'\n=== STEP 4: BOOK CANDIDATE ANALYSIS ===') if book_candidates: print(f'\nAnalyzing {len(book_candidates)} potential book titles:') # Sort by evidence strength sorted_candidates = sorted(book_candidates.items(), key=lambda x: len(x[1]), reverse=True) for title, evidence_list in sorted_candidates[:10]: # Top 10 candidates print(f'\nüìö CANDIDATE: {title}') print(f' Evidence sources: {len(evidence_list)}') # Aggregate terms and scores all_terms = set() total_score = 0 sources = set() for evidence in evidence_list: all_terms.update(evidence['terms']) total_score += evidence['score'] sources.add(evidence['query']) print(f' Key terms found: {sorted(list(all_terms))}') print(f' Total relevance score: {total_score}') print(f' Search queries: {len(sources)}') # Check for four-volume edition indicators title_lower = title.lower() if any(indicator in title_lower for indicator in ['four volume', '4 volume', 'vol.', 'volume']): print(f' ‚úì VOLUME INDICATOR FOUND') # Check for 1877-1878 date indicators if any(year in title_lower for year in ['1877', '1878']): print(f' ‚úì TARGET PUBLICATION YEARS FOUND') print('-' * 100) else: print('\n‚ö† No clear book candidates identified from search results') print(f'\n=== STEP 5: DETAILED ANALYSIS OF HIGH-PRIORITY FINDINGS ===') if high_priority_findings: # Sort by priority and score high_priority_findings.sort(key=lambda x: (x['priority'].startswith('HIGH'), len(x['key_terms_found']), x['score']), reverse=True) print(f'\nAnalyzing top {min(10, len(high_priority_findings))} high-priority findings:') for i, finding in enumerate(high_priority_findings[:10], 1): print(f'\nüîç FINDING {i} - {finding["priority"]} (Score: {finding["score"]})') print(f'Query: {finding["query"]}') print(f'Key terms: {finding["key_terms_found"]}') print(f'URL: {finding["url"]}') print(f'Text: {finding["text"][:500]}...') # Try Google Books API for more specific results print(f'\n=== STEP 6: GOOGLE BOOKS API SEARCH ===') google_books_queries = [ 'Harriet Martineau History of the Peace 1877', 'Martineau History England four volumes 1878', 'Harriet Martineau Convention London 1840', 'Martineau Egyptian Ottoman crisis 1846' ] books_api_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(google_books_queries, 1): print(f'\n--- Google Books API Query {i}: {query} ---') try: api_url = 'https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes' params = { 'q': query, 'maxResults': 20, 'printType': 'books' } response = requests.get(api_url, params=params, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: data = response.json() if 'items' in data: print(f'Found {len(data["items"])} books') for book in data['items']: volume_info = book.get('volumeInfo', {}) title = volume_info.get('title', '') authors = volume_info.get('authors', []) published_date = volume_info.get('publishedDate', '') publisher = volume_info.get('publisher', '') description = volume_info.get('description', '') # Check if this matches our criteria title_lower = title.lower() authors_str = ' '.join(authors).lower() if authors else '' desc_lower = description.lower() # Look for Martineau and relevant terms if 'martineau' in authors_str or 'martineau' in title_lower: relevance_score = 0 # Score based on key terms key_indicators = [ ('1877', 3), ('1878', 3), ('1846', 2), ('1840', 2), ('history', 2), ('peace', 2), ('convention', 2), ('london', 1), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('four volume', 4), ('volume', 1) ] combined_text = f'{title_lower} {desc_lower} {published_date}' for indicator, score in key_indicators: if indicator in combined_text: relevance_score += score if relevance_score >= 3: # Significant relevance print(f'\nüéØ RELEVANT BOOK FOUND (Score: {relevance_score})!') print(f'Title: {title}') print(f'Authors: {authors}') print(f'Publisher: {publisher}') print(f'Published: {published_date}') if description: print(f'Description: {description[:300]}...') books_api_results.append({ 'title': title, 'authors': authors, 'publisher': publisher, 'published_date': published_date, 'description': description, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'query': query, 'source': 'Google Books API' }) else: print('No books found in API response') else: print(f'API request failed: {response.status_code}') time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting except Exception as e: print(f'Error with Google Books API: {str(e)}') # Save comprehensive analysis analysis_results = { 'search_objective': 'Find Harriet Martineau book on European peace ending 1846', 'key_elements': { 'period_ending': 1846, 'convention_of_london': 1840, 'egyptian_ottoman_crisis': True, 'four_volume_edition': '1877-1878' }, 'search_summary': { 'total_queries': len(search_queries), 'successful_searches': successful_searches, 'total_relevant_links': sum(len(r['relevant_links']) for r in search_results.values()), 'google_books_results': len(books_api_results) }, 'analysis_results': { 'high_priority_findings': len(high_priority_findings), 'book_candidates': len(book_candidates), 'historical_terms_frequency': historical_terms_frequency, 'top_book_candidates': list(book_candidates.keys())[:5] if book_candidates else [] }, 'high_priority_findings': high_priority_findings[:15], # Top 15 findings 'google_books_results': books_api_results, 'search_queries_used': search_queries, 'analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } analysis_file = 'workspace/martineau_european_peace_book_search_analysis.json' with open(analysis_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\n*** MARTINEAU BOOK SEARCH ANALYSIS COMPLETE ***') print(f'‚úì Conducted {successful_searches} successful web searches') print(f'‚úì Analyzed {sum(len(r["relevant_links"]) for r in search_results.values())} relevant results') print(f'‚úì Found {len(high_priority_findings)} high-priority findings') print(f'‚úì Identified {len(book_candidates)} potential book candidates') print(f'‚úì Found {len(books_api_results)} relevant books via Google Books API') print(f'‚úì Comprehensive analysis saved to: {analysis_file}') # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json import time from urllib.parse import quote_plus print('=== FIXED: SEARCHING FOR HARRIET MARTINEAU\'S BOOK ON EUROPEAN PEACE ENDING 1846 ===') print('Objective: Find Martineau book analyzing European peace period ending 1846') print('Key elements: Convention of London 1840, Egyptian-Ottoman crisis') print('Target: Four-volume edition published 1877-1878') print('\n' + '='*100 + '\n') # Ensure workspace directory exists os.makedirs('workspace', exist_ok=True) # First, let's check if we have any existing analysis file to understand the current state analysis_file = 'workspace/martineau_european_peace_book_search_analysis.json' if os.path.exists(analysis_file): print('=== INSPECTING EXISTING ANALYSIS FILE ===') try: with open(analysis_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: existing_data = json.load(f) print('File structure inspection:') for key in existing_data.keys(): print(f' - {key}: {type(existing_data[key])}') if 'google_books_results' in existing_data: print(f'\nGoogle Books results found: {len(existing_data["google_books_results"])} books') for i, book in enumerate(existing_data['google_books_results'][:3], 1): print(f' {i}. {book.get("title", "No title")} (Score: {book.get("relevance_score", 0)})') if 'search_summary' in existing_data: print(f'\nPrevious search summary:') summary = existing_data['search_summary'] for key, value in summary.items(): print(f' - {key}: {value}') except Exception as e: print(f'Error reading existing analysis: {str(e)}') # Define comprehensive search queries based on the PLAN search_queries = [ 'Harriet Martineau European peace 1846', 'Convention of London 1840 Martineau', 'Egyptian-Ottoman crisis Martineau book', 'Martineau four-volume edition 1877 1878', 'Harriet Martineau diplomatic history Europe 1840s', 'Martineau Convention London Egyptian crisis', 'Harriet Martineau European diplomacy 1846', 'Martineau Ottoman Empire Egypt 1840 book', 'Harriet Martineau history peace Europe 1840s', 'Martineau four volumes 1877 1878 European history' ] print('\n=== STEP 1: CONDUCTING TARGETED SEARCHES FOR MARTINEAU\'S HISTORICAL WORK ===') print(f'Total search queries: {len(search_queries)}') print('\nSearch queries:') for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f' {i:2d}. {query}') search_results = {} # Function to perform search and analyze results - FIXED HEADERS SCOPE ISSUE def perform_search(query, search_index): # Define headers INSIDE the function to fix scope issue headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.5', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1', 'Cache-Control': 'no-cache', 'Pragma': 'no-cache' } search_base_url = 'https://html.duckduckgo.com/html/' print(f'\n--- SEARCH {search_index}: {query} ---') try: params = {'q': query} response = requests.get(search_base_url, params=params, headers=headers, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: # Save raw HTML for analysis - FIXED FILENAME GENERATION clean_query = query.replace(' ', '_').replace("'", '').replace('"', '').replace('/', '_') filename = f"martineau_search_{search_index:02d}_{clean_query[:40]}.html" filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) with open(filepath, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'Saved: {filepath}') # Parse for relevant results soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser') # Look for result links with historical book information result_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href') text = link.get_text().strip() # Filter for highly relevant results if href and text and len(text) > 15: text_lower = text.lower() relevance_score = 0 # High-value terms for Martineau's historical work high_value_terms = [ ('harriet martineau', 3), ('martineau', 2), ('1846', 3), ('1840', 2), ('convention of london', 4), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('crisis', 1), ('european peace', 3), ('diplomatic', 2), ('diplomacy', 2), ('four volume', 3), ('1877', 2), ('1878', 2), ('history', 1), ('historical', 1), ('peace', 1), ('europe', 1) ] # Book-specific terms book_terms = [ ('history of england', 3), ('history of the peace', 4), ('eastern question', 3), ('thirty years peace', 4), ('england and her soldiers', 2), ('biographical sketches', 2) ] # Calculate relevance score for term, score in high_value_terms + book_terms: if term in text_lower: relevance_score += score # Additional scoring for URL domains if href: href_lower = href.lower() if any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['archive.org', 'gutenberg.org', 'hathitrust.org', 'google.com/books']): relevance_score += 3 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['wikipedia.org', 'britannica.com', 'jstor.org']): relevance_score += 2 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['amazon.com', 'worldcat.org', 'goodreads.com']): relevance_score += 1 if relevance_score >= 3: # Only include highly relevant results result_links.append({ 'url': href, 'text': text[:400], # Longer text for better analysis 'relevance_score': relevance_score }) # Sort by relevance score result_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) search_results[query] = { 'html_file': filepath, 'status_code': response.status_code, 'relevant_links': result_links[:20], # Top 20 most relevant 'total_links_found': len(result_links) } print(f'Found {len(result_links)} highly relevant links') if result_links: print('Top results:') for i, link in enumerate(result_links[:5], 1): print(f' {i}. Score {link["relevance_score"]}: {link["text"][:120]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') time.sleep(2) # Rate limiting return True else: print(f'Failed: HTTP {response.status_code}') return False except Exception as e: print(f'Error: {str(e)}') return False # Perform all searches print('\n=== EXECUTING SEARCHES ===') successful_searches = 0 for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): if perform_search(query, i): successful_searches += 1 # Brief pause between searches if i < len(search_queries): time.sleep(1) print(f'\n=== STEP 2: ANALYZING SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK IDENTIFICATION ===') print(f'Successful searches: {successful_searches}/{len(search_queries)}') # Compile and analyze all findings high_priority_findings = [] book_candidates = {} historical_terms_frequency = {} # Key terms to track for book identification key_terms = [ 'history of england', 'history of the peace', 'thirty years peace', 'eastern question', 'convention of london', 'egyptian crisis', 'ottoman crisis', 'four volume', '1877', '1878', '1846', '1840' ] print('\n--- ANALYZING ALL SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK PATTERNS ---') for query, results in search_results.items(): print(f'\nQuery: "{query}"') print(f' Relevant links: {results["total_links_found"]}') for link in results['relevant_links']: text_lower = link['text'].lower() # Check for key historical terms found_terms = [] for term in key_terms: if term in text_lower: found_terms.append(term) historical_terms_frequency[term] = historical_terms_frequency.get(term, 0) + 1 # High-priority: Contains multiple key terms if len(found_terms) >= 3: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'HIGH - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üéØ HIGH PRIORITY: {len(found_terms)} key terms found: {found_terms}') # Try to extract potential book titles text_lines = link['text'].split('\n') for line in text_lines: line_lower = line.lower().strip() if ('history' in line_lower and ('martineau' in line_lower or len(line.strip()) > 20) and any(term in line_lower for term in ['peace', 'england', 'thirty years'])): # This might be a book title potential_title = line.strip()[:200] if potential_title not in book_candidates: book_candidates[potential_title] = [] book_candidates[potential_title].append({ 'query': query, 'url': link['url'], 'terms': found_terms, 'score': link['relevance_score'] }) elif len(found_terms) >= 2: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'MEDIUM - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üìç MEDIUM: {len(found_terms)} key terms: {found_terms}') print(f'\n=== STEP 3: HISTORICAL TERMS FREQUENCY ANALYSIS ===') print(f'Total high-priority findings: {len(high_priority_findings)}') print(f'Potential book candidates identified: {len(book_candidates)}') if historical_terms_frequency: print('\nHistorical terms frequency:') sorted_terms = sorted(historical_terms_frequency.items(), key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True) for term, count in sorted_terms: print(f' {term}: {count} mentions') else: print('\nNo specific historical terms clearly identified') # Enhanced Google Books API search with more specific queries print(f'\n=== STEP 4: ENHANCED GOOGLE BOOKS API SEARCH ===') # More targeted queries based on likely Martineau works google_books_queries = [ 'Harriet Martineau "History of the Peace" 1877', 'Martineau "History of England" four volumes 1878', 'Harriet Martineau "Thirty Years Peace" 1877 1878', 'Martineau "Eastern Question" Convention London 1840', 'Harriet Martineau biographical sketches 1877', 'Martineau history peace Europe 1815 1846' ] books_api_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(google_books_queries, 1): print(f'\n--- Google Books API Query {i}: {query} ---') try: api_url = 'https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes' params = { 'q': query, 'maxResults': 20, 'printType': 'books' } response = requests.get(api_url, params=params, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: data = response.json() if 'items' in data: print(f'Found {len(data["items"])} books') for book in data['items']: volume_info = book.get('volumeInfo', {}) title = volume_info.get('title', '') authors = volume_info.get('authors', []) published_date = volume_info.get('publishedDate', '') publisher = volume_info.get('publisher', '') description = volume_info.get('description', '') # Check if this matches our criteria title_lower = title.lower() authors_str = ' '.join(authors).lower() if authors else '' desc_lower = description.lower() # Look for Martineau and relevant terms if 'martineau' in authors_str or 'martineau' in title_lower: relevance_score = 0 # Score based on key terms with enhanced scoring key_indicators = [ ('1877', 4), ('1878', 4), ('1846', 3), ('1840', 3), ('history of the peace', 5), ('history of england', 4), ('thirty years peace', 5), ('eastern question', 4), ('convention of london', 4), ('biographical sketches', 3), ('history', 2), ('peace', 2), ('convention', 2), ('london', 1), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('four volume', 5), ('volume', 1), ('diplomatic', 2) ] combined_text = f'{title_lower} {desc_lower} {published_date}' for indicator, score in key_indicators: if indicator in combined_text: relevance_score += score if relevance_score >= 3: # Significant relevance print(f'\nüéØ RELEVANT BOOK FOUND (Score: {relevance_score})!') print(f'Title: {title}') print(f'Authors: {authors}') print(f'Publisher: {publisher}') print(f'Published: {published_date}') if description: print(f'Description: {description[:300]}...') # Check for four-volume indicators if any(vol_indicator in combined_text for vol_indicator in ['four volume', '4 volume', 'vol. 1', 'vol. 2', 'vol. 3', 'vol. 4']): print(' ‚úì VOLUME INDICATOR DETECTED') # Rate limiting except Exception as e: print(f'Error with Google Books API: {str(e)}') # Save comprehensive analysis analysis_results = { 'search_objective': 'Find Harriet Martineau book on European peace ending 1846', 'key_elements': { 'period_ending': 1846, 'convention_of_london': 1840, 'egyptian_ottoman_crisis': True, 'four_volume_edition': '1877-1878' }, 'search_summary': { 'total_queries': len(search_queries), 'successful_searches': successful_searches, 'total_relevant_links': sum(len(r['relevant_links']) for r in search_results.values()), 'google_books_results': len(books_api_results) }, 'analysis_results': { 'high_priority_findings': len(high_priority_findings), 'book_candidates': len(book_candidates), 'historical_terms_frequency': historical_terms_frequency, 'top_book_candidates': list(book_candidates.keys())[:5] if book_candidates else [] }, 'high_priority_findings': high_priority_findings[:15], # Top 15 findings 'google_books_results': books_api_results, 'search_queries_used': search_queries, 'analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } analysis_file = 'workspace/martineau_european_peace_book_search_analysis_fixed.json' with open(analysis_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\n*** MARTINEAU BOOK SEARCH ANALYSIS COMPLETE ***') print(f'‚úì Conducted {successful_searches} successful web searches') print(f'‚úì Analyzed {sum(len(r["relevant_links"]) for r in search_results.values())} relevant results') print(f'‚úì Found {len(high_priority_findings)} high-priority findings') print(f'‚úì Identified {len(book_candidates)} potential book candidates') print(f'‚úì Found {len(books_api_results)} relevant books via Google Books API') print(f'‚úì Comprehensive analysis saved to: {analysis_file}') # import os import requests from bs4 import BeautifulSoup import json import time from urllib.parse import quote_plus print('=== FIXED: SEARCHING FOR HARRIET MARTINEAU\'S BOOK ON EUROPEAN PEACE ENDING 1846 ===') print('Objective: Find Martineau book analyzing European peace period ending 1846') print('Key elements: Convention of London 1840, Egyptian-Ottoman crisis') print('Target: Four-volume edition published 1877-1878') print('\n' + '='*100 + '\n') # Ensure workspace directory exists os.makedirs('workspace', exist_ok=True) # First, let's check if we have any existing analysis file to understand the current state analysis_file = 'workspace/martineau_european_peace_book_search_analysis.json' if os.path.exists(analysis_file): print('=== INSPECTING EXISTING ANALYSIS FILE ===') try: with open(analysis_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: existing_data = json.load(f) print('File structure inspection:') for key in existing_data.keys(): print(f' - {key}: {type(existing_data[key])}') if 'google_books_results' in existing_data: print(f'\nGoogle Books results found: {len(existing_data["google_books_results"])} books') for i, book in enumerate(existing_data['google_books_results'][:3], 1): print(f' {i}. {book.get("title", "No title")} (Score: {book.get("relevance_score", 0)})') if 'search_summary' in existing_data: print(f'\nPrevious search summary:') summary = existing_data['search_summary'] for key, value in summary.items(): print(f' - {key}: {value}') except Exception as e: print(f'Error reading existing analysis: {str(e)}') # Define comprehensive search queries based on the PLAN search_queries = [ 'Harriet Martineau European peace 1846', 'Convention of London 1840 Martineau', 'Egyptian-Ottoman crisis Martineau book', 'Martineau four-volume edition 1877 1878', 'Harriet Martineau diplomatic history Europe 1840s', 'Martineau Convention London Egyptian crisis', 'Harriet Martineau European diplomacy 1846', 'Martineau Ottoman Empire Egypt 1840 book', 'Harriet Martineau history peace Europe 1840s', 'Martineau four volumes 1877 1878 European history' ] print('\n=== STEP 1: CONDUCTING TARGETED SEARCHES FOR MARTINEAU\'S HISTORICAL WORK ===') print(f'Total search queries: {len(search_queries)}') print('\nSearch queries:') for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): print(f' {i:2d}. {query}') search_results = {} # Function to perform search and analyze results - FIXED HEADERS SCOPE ISSUE def perform_search(query, search_index): # Define headers INSIDE the function to fix scope issue headers = { 'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0 (Windows NT 10.0; Win64; x64) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Chrome/91.0.4472.124 Safari/537.36', 'Accept': 'text/html,application/xhtml+xml,application/xml;q=0.9,image/webp,*/*;q=0.8', 'Accept-Language': 'en-US,en;q=0.5', 'Accept-Encoding': 'gzip, deflate, br', 'Connection': 'keep-alive', 'Upgrade-Insecure-Requests': '1', 'Cache-Control': 'no-cache', 'Pragma': 'no-cache' } search_base_url = 'https://html.duckduckgo.com/html/' print(f'\n--- SEARCH {search_index}: {query} ---') try: params = {'q': query} response = requests.get(search_base_url, params=params, headers=headers, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: # Save raw HTML for analysis - FIXED FILENAME GENERATION clean_query = query.replace(' ', '_').replace("'", '').replace('"', '').replace('/', '_') filename = f"martineau_search_{search_index:02d}_{clean_query[:40]}.html" filepath = os.path.join('workspace', filename) with open(filepath, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: f.write(response.text) print(f'Saved: {filepath}') # Parse for relevant results soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser') # Look for result links with historical book information result_links = [] for link in soup.find_all('a', href=True): href = link.get('href') text = link.get_text().strip() # Filter for highly relevant results if href and text and len(text) > 15: text_lower = text.lower() relevance_score = 0 # High-value terms for Martineau's historical work high_value_terms = [ ('harriet martineau', 3), ('martineau', 2), ('1846', 3), ('1840', 2), ('convention of london', 4), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('crisis', 1), ('european peace', 3), ('diplomatic', 2), ('diplomacy', 2), ('four volume', 3), ('1877', 2), ('1878', 2), ('history', 1), ('historical', 1), ('peace', 1), ('europe', 1) ] # Book-specific terms book_terms = [ ('history of england', 3), ('history of the peace', 4), ('eastern question', 3), ('thirty years peace', 4), ('england and her soldiers', 2), ('biographical sketches', 2) ] # Calculate relevance score for term, score in high_value_terms + book_terms: if term in text_lower: relevance_score += score # Additional scoring for URL domains if href: href_lower = href.lower() if any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['archive.org', 'gutenberg.org', 'hathitrust.org', 'google.com/books']): relevance_score += 3 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['wikipedia.org', 'britannica.com', 'jstor.org']): relevance_score += 2 elif any(domain in href_lower for domain in ['amazon.com', 'worldcat.org', 'goodreads.com']): relevance_score += 1 if relevance_score >= 3: # Only include highly relevant results result_links.append({ 'url': href, 'text': text[:400], # Longer text for better analysis 'relevance_score': relevance_score }) # Sort by relevance score result_links.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) search_results[query] = { 'html_file': filepath, 'status_code': response.status_code, 'relevant_links': result_links[:20], # Top 20 most relevant 'total_links_found': len(result_links) } print(f'Found {len(result_links)} highly relevant links') if result_links: print('Top results:') for i, link in enumerate(result_links[:5], 1): print(f' {i}. Score {link["relevance_score"]}: {link["text"][:120]}...') print(f' URL: {link["url"]}') time.sleep(2) # Rate limiting return True else: print(f'Failed: HTTP {response.status_code}') return False except Exception as e: print(f'Error: {str(e)}') return False # Perform all searches print('\n=== EXECUTING SEARCHES ===') successful_searches = 0 for i, query in enumerate(search_queries, 1): if perform_search(query, i): successful_searches += 1 # Brief pause between searches if i < len(search_queries): time.sleep(1) print(f'\n=== STEP 2: ANALYZING SEARCH RESULTS FOR BOOK IDENTIFICATION ===') print(f'Successful searches: {successful_searches}/{len(search_queries)}') # Check for key historical terms found_terms = [] for term in key_terms: if term in text_lower: found_terms.append(term) historical_terms_frequency[term] = historical_terms_frequency.get(term, 0) + 1 # High-priority: Contains multiple key terms if len(found_terms) >= 3: high_priority_findings.append({ 'query': query, 'text': link['text'], 'url': link['url'], 'score': link['relevance_score'], 'key_terms_found': found_terms, 'priority': f'HIGH - {len(found_terms)} key terms' }) print(f' üéØ HIGH PRIORITY: {len(found_terms)} key terms found: {found_terms}') # Try to extract potential book titles text_lines = link['text'].split('\n') for line in text_lines: line_lower = line.lower().strip() if ('history' in line_lower and ('martineau' in line_lower or len(line.strip()) > 20) and any(term in line_lower for term in ['peace', 'england', 'thirty years'])): # ENDING 1846 ===') print('Objective: Find Martineau book analyzing European peace period ending 1846') print('Key elements: Convention of London 1840, Egyptian-Ottoman crisis') print('Target: Four-volume edition published 1877-1878') print('\n' + '='*100 + '\n') # Ensure workspace directory exists os.makedirs('workspace', exist_ok=True) # First, let's check if we have any existing analysis file to understand the current state analysis_file = 'workspace/martineau_european_peace_book_search_analysis.json' if os.path.exists(analysis_file): print('=== INSPECTING EXISTING ANALYSIS FILE ===') try: with open(analysis_file, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f: existing_data = json.load(f) print('File structure inspection:') for key in existing_data.keys(): print(f' - {key}: {type(existing_data[key])}') if 'google_books_results' in existing_data: print(f'\nGoogle Books results found: {len(existing_data["google_books_results"])} books') for i, book in enumerate(existing_data['google_books_results'][:3], 1): print(f' {i}. {book.get("title", "No title")} (Score: {book.get("relevance_score", 0)})') if 'search_summary' in existing_data: print(f'\nPrevious search summary:') summary = existing_data['search_summary'] for key, value in summary.items(): print(f' - {key}: {value}') except Exception as e: print(f'Error reading existing analysis: {str(e)}') # Since web searches are failing with 202 errors, focus on comprehensive Google Books API search print('\n=== COMPREHENSIVE GOOGLE BOOKS API SEARCH ===') print('Note: Web searches returning 202 errors, focusing on Google Books API for reliable results') # Comprehensive Google Books API queries targeting Martineau's historical works google_books_queries = [ 'Harriet Martineau "History of the Peace" 1877', 'Martineau "History of England" four volumes 1878', 'Harriet Martineau "Thirty Years Peace" 1877 1878', 'Martineau "Eastern Question" Convention London 1840', 'Harriet Martineau biographical sketches 1877', 'Martineau history peace Europe 1815 1846', 'Harriet Martineau "History of Peace" four volume', 'Martineau diplomatic history 1840s Egyptian Ottoman', 'Harriet Martineau England peace 1877 1878 volumes', 'Martineau Convention London 1840 Egyptian crisis book' ] books_api_results = [] for i, query in enumerate(google_books_queries, 1): print(f'\n--- Google Books API Query {i}: {query} ---') try: api_url = 'https://www.googleapis.com/books/v1/volumes' params = { 'q': query, 'maxResults': 20, 'printType': 'books' } response = requests.get(api_url, params=params, timeout=30) print(f'Status: {response.status_code}') if response.status_code == 200: data = response.json() if 'items' in data: print(f'Found {len(data["items"])} books') for book in data['items']: volume_info = book.get('volumeInfo', {}) title = volume_info.get('title', '') authors = volume_info.get('authors', []) published_date = volume_info.get('publishedDate', '') publisher = volume_info.get('publisher', '') description = volume_info.get('description', '') # Check if this matches our criteria title_lower = title.lower() authors_str = ' '.join(authors).lower() if authors else '' desc_lower = description.lower() # Look for Martineau and relevant terms if 'martineau' in authors_str or 'martineau' in title_lower: relevance_score = 0 # Score based on key terms with enhanced scoring - FIXED VARIABLE SCOPE key_indicators = [ ('1877', 4), ('1878', 4), ('1846', 3), ('1840', 3), ('history of the peace', 5), ('history of england', 4), ('thirty years peace', 5), ('eastern question', 4), ('convention of london', 4), ('biographical sketches', 3), ('history', 2), ('peace', 2), ('convention', 2), ('london', 1), ('egyptian', 2), ('ottoman', 2), ('four volume', 5), ('volume', 1), ('diplomatic', 2) ] # FIXED: Define combined_text properly within scope combined_text = f'{title_lower} {desc_lower} {published_date}' for indicator, score in key_indicators: if indicator in combined_text: relevance_score += score if relevance_score >= 3: # Significant relevance print(f'\nüéØ RELEVANT BOOK FOUND (Score: {relevance_score})!') print(f'Title: {title}') print(f'Authors: {authors}') print(f'Publisher: {publisher}') print(f'Published: {published_date}') if description: print(f'Description: {description[:300]}...') # Check for four-volume indicators if any(vol_indicator in combined_text for vol_indicator in ['four volume', '4 volume', 'vol. 1', 'vol. 2', 'vol. 3', 'vol. 4']): print(' ‚úì VOLUME INDICATOR DETECTED') # Check for target years if '1877' in combined_text or '1878' in combined_text: print(' ‚úì TARGET PUBLICATION YEARS DETECTED') # Check for key historical events if 'convention' in combined_text and 'london' in combined_text: print(' ‚úì CONVENTION OF LONDON REFERENCE DETECTED') if 'egyptian' in combined_text or 'ottoman' in combined_text: print(' ‚úì EGYPTIAN-OTTOMAN CRISIS REFERENCE DETECTED') books_api_results.append({ 'title': title, 'authors': authors, 'publisher': publisher, 'published_date': published_date, 'description': description, 'relevance_score': relevance_score, 'query': query, 'source': 'Google Books API', 'has_volume_indicator': any(vol_indicator in combined_text for vol_indicator in ['four volume', '4 volume', 'vol. 1', 'vol. 2', 'vol. 3', 'vol. 4']), 'has_target_years': '1877' in combined_text or '1878' in combined_text, 'has_convention_london': 'convention' in combined_text and 'london' in combined_text, 'has_egyptian_ottoman': 'egyptian' in combined_text or 'ottoman' in combined_text }) else: print('No books found in API response') else: print(f'API request failed: {response.status_code}') time.sleep(1) # Rate limiting except Exception as e: print(f'Error with Google Books API: {str(e)}') # Analyze and rank the results print(f'\n=== ANALYSIS OF GOOGLE BOOKS API RESULTS ===') print(f'Total relevant books found: {len(books_api_results)}') if books_api_results: # Sort by relevance score books_api_results.sort(key=lambda x: x['relevance_score'], reverse=True) print(f'\nüìö TOP BOOK CANDIDATES (sorted by relevance):') for i, book in enumerate(books_api_results[:10], 1): # Top 10 candidates print(f'\n{i}. {book["title"]} (Score: {book["relevance_score"]})') print(f' Authors: {book["authors"]}') print(f' Published: {book["published_date"]}') print(f' Publisher: {book["publisher"]}') # Show key indicators indicators = [] if book['has_target_years']: indicators.append('‚úì 1877-1878 years') if book['has_volume_indicator']: indicators.append('‚úì Volume indicator') if book['has_convention_london']: indicators.append('‚úì Convention of London') if book['has_egyptian_ottoman']: indicators.append('‚úì Egyptian-Ottoman') if indicators: print(f' Key matches: {" | ".join(indicators)}') # Show description excerpt if book['description']: print(f' Description: {book["description"][:200]}...') print('-' * 100) # Identify the most likely candidate top_candidate = books_api_results[0] print(f'\nüèÜ MOST LIKELY CANDIDATE:') print(f'Title: {top_candidate["title"]}') print(f'Authors: {top_candidate["authors"]}') print(f'Published: {top_candidate["published_date"]}') print(f'Relevance Score: {top_candidate["relevance_score"]}') # Check if this matches our target criteria criteria_matches = [] if top_candidate['has_target_years']: criteria_matches.append('Publication years 1877-1878') if top_candidate['has_volume_indicator']: criteria_matches.append('Multi-volume edition') if top_candidate['has_convention_london']: criteria_matches.append('Convention of London 1840') if top_candidate['has_egyptian_ottoman']: criteria_matches.append('Egyptian-Ottoman crisis') if criteria_matches: print(f'\n‚úì MATCHES TARGET CRITERIA:') for match in criteria_matches: print(f' - {match}') else: print(f'\n‚ö† Does not fully match target criteria, but highest relevance') # Look for books specifically about "History of the Peace" peace_history_books = [book for book in books_api_results if 'history of the peace' in book['title'].lower() or 'thirty years peace' in book['title'].lower()] if peace_history_books: print(f'\nüìñ BOOKS SPECIFICALLY ABOUT "HISTORY OF THE PEACE":') for book in peace_history_books: print(f'- {book["title"]} ({book["published_date"]}) - Score: {book["relevance_score"]}') # Look for books from 1877-1878 specifically target_year_books = [book for book in books_api_results if book['has_target_years']] if target_year_books: print(f'\nüìÖ BOOKS FROM TARGET YEARS 1877-1878:') for book in target_year_books: print(f'- {book["title"]} ({book["published_date"]}) - Score: {book["relevance_score"]}') if book['has_volume_indicator']: print(f' ‚úì Multi-volume edition detected') else: print('\n‚ö† No relevant books found via Google Books API') # Save comprehensive analysis with fixed structure analysis_results = { 'search_objective': 'Find Harriet Martineau book on European peace ending 1846', 'key_elements': { 'period_ending': 1846, 'convention_of_london': 1840, 'egyptian_ottoman_crisis': True, 'four_volume_edition': '1877-1878' }, 'search_summary': { 'web_searches_attempted': 10, 'web_searches_successful': 0, 'web_search_status': 'Failed - HTTP 202 errors', 'google_books_queries': len(google_books_queries), 'google_books_results': len(books_api_results) }, 'analysis_results': { 'total_relevant_books': len(books_api_results), 'books_with_target_years': len([b for b in books_api_results if b['has_target_years']]), 'books_with_volume_indicators': len([b for b in books_api_results if b['has_volume_indicator']]), 'books_with_convention_london': len([b for b in books_api_results if b['has_convention_london']]), 'books_with_egyptian_ottoman': len([b for b in books_api_results if b['has_egyptian_ottoman']]) }, 'google_books_results': books_api_results, 'top_candidate': books_api_results[0] if books_api_results else None, 'search_queries_used': google_books_queries, 'analysis_timestamp': time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S') } analysis_file = 'workspace/martineau_european_peace_final_analysis.json' with open(analysis_file, 'w', encoding='utf-8') as f: json.dump(analysis_results, f, indent=2, ensure_ascii=False) print(f'\n*** MARTINEAU BOOK SEARCH ANALYSIS COMPLETE ***') print(f'‚úì Web searches: 0/10 successful (HTTP 202 errors)') print(f'‚úì Google Books API searches: {len(google_books_queries)} queries executed') print(f'‚úì Found {len(books_api_results)} relevant books via Google Books API') print(f'‚úì Comprehensive analysis saved to: {analysis_file}') if books_api_results: print(f'\nüéØ FINAL CONCLUSION:') top_book = books_api_results[0] print(f'Most likely book: {top_book["title"]}') print(f'Authors: {top_book["authors"]}') print(f'Published: {top_book["published_date"]}') print(f'Relevance Score: {top_book["relevance_score"]}') # Determine if this is likely the target book if top_book['has_target_years'] and (top_book['has_volume_indicator'] or top_book['relevance_score'] >= 8): print(f'\n‚úÖ HIGH CONFIDENCE: This appears to be the target book based on:') print(f' - Publication in target years (1877-1878)') if top_book['has_volume_indicator']: print(f' - Multi-volume edition indicator') if top_book['has_convention_london']: print(f' - References to Convention of London') if top_book['has_egyptian_ottoman']: print(f' - References to Egyptian-Ottoman crisis') else: print(f'\n‚ö† MEDIUM CONFIDENCE: Partial match - may need further investigation') else: print(f'\n‚ö† No definitive book identification completed') print('Recommend checking historical databases or library catalogs')
